text:
I want to motivate
and enable members

of the Hispanic community to
dream big and dream often.

I want to mentor those
who are too often told

to lower their standards
for success simply

because of their
name, how they look,
or how much their family makes.

I want to champion the
vibrant Hispanic culture here

in the United States,
encouraging others to celebrate

and never hide where
they come from.

I want to be a loyal brother,
son, friend, and leader who

is never too busy to
listen, share a laugh,

I want to challenge myself
to be more than I ever

thought I was capable
of and never let fear
I want to enjoy the ride.
